 Supreme Court Justice, Sylvester Nwali Ngwuta, is dead. According to reports, late Sylvester died in his sleep on Sunday, March 7 at his official residence in Abuja. The senior judge who had an encounter with the current administration in 2017 was getting ready for his retirement after clocking 70 years on March 30th, 2020. May his soul rest in perfect peace. More details to follow